# Negotiation Engine — Orakara

## Overview

The negotiation engine is the core of Orakara. It governs how a buyer and seller move from an initial inquiry to a signed deal, enforcing stage sequencing, turn ownership, and time boundaries at every step.

The engine is implemented as a deterministic state machine in `src/lib/negotiationOrchestrator.ts`, with a companion `src/lib/dealFlow.ts` handling post-deal milestone progression.

---

## Stage Sequence

Every negotiation passes through stages in order. A stage cannot be entered until the preceding stage is complete. A stage cannot be skipped except where explicitly permitted (sample is optional).

```
PENDING
  ↓ (seller may request clarification first)
CLARIFICATION_NEEDED → CLARIFICATION_ANSWERED
  ↓
RESPONDED
  ↓ (buyer initiates negotiation)
NEGOTIATING_SPECS
  ↓ (all specs agreed + timer not expired)
SAMPLE_REQUESTED ──(optional)──→ SAMPLE_APPROVED
         ↓ (or buyer skips sample)           ↓
         └──────────────────────────→ NEGOTIATING_PRICE
                                             ↓ (price + payment mode + quantity + lead time + tranches agreed)
                                      NEGOTIATING_CONTRACT
                                             ↓ (both parties sign or skip + timer expires)
                                        DEAL_CREATED

At any active stage:
  → WITHDRAWN   (either party withdraws)
  → EXPIRED     (timer reaches deadline)
  → FAILED      (final offer rejected / system timeout)
  → DECLINED    (seller declines at intake)
```

