## Timer System

Every negotiation stage has a time boundary. When the timer expires, the inquiry fails automatically. Timers support pause, resume, extension requests, holiday awareness, and admin override.

### Timer fields (`NegotiationTimer`)

```
startedAt        DateTime   — creation timestamp
deadline         DateTime   — hard expiry (startedAt + configured hours per stage)
paused           Boolean    — current pause state
pausedAt         DateTime   — when paused
remainingSeconds Int        — seconds remaining, stored at pause time; cleared on resume
expired          Boolean    — set true by cron
expiredAt        DateTime   — when marked expired
```

### Pause logic

```typescript
// pauseTimer(timerId)
const remainingMs = deadline.getTime() - Date.now();
const remainingSeconds = Math.floor(remainingMs / 1000);
await prisma.negotiationTimer.update({
  where: { id: timerId },
  data: { paused: true, pausedAt: new Date(), remainingSeconds }
});
```

### Resume logic

```typescript
// resumeTimer(timerId)
const newDeadline = new Date(Date.now() + timer.remainingSeconds * 1000);
await prisma.negotiationTimer.update({
  where: { id: timerId },
  data: {
    paused: false,
    pausedAt: null,
    remainingSeconds: null,
    deadline: newDeadline
  }
});
```

Resuming always resets the deadline to `now + remainingSeconds`. The original `startedAt` is preserved as a record but the effective expiry moves forward.

### Expiry check

```typescript
function isTimerExpired(timer: NegotiationTimer): boolean {
  if (timer.paused) return false; // paused timers can never expire
  return new Date() > timer.deadline;
}
```

A paused timer is immune to expiry. This is the invariant that makes holiday pausing safe — no deal can be timed out while timers are paused.

### Extension flow

Either party can request a 24-hour extension via `POST /api/inquiries/[id]/timer/extend`. The counterparty must accept. If accepted, `deadline += 24 hours` (added to the *current* deadline, not to now). A `TimerExtension` record is created with `ExtensionStatus.PENDING` → `ACCEPTED` / `DECLINED`.

Admin can override without counterparty consent via `POST /api/admin/timers/[timerId]/extend`, logged to `AdminTimerOverride` and `AuditLog`.

### Holiday pausing

`processHolidayStart(countryCode)` pauses *all* active timers for that country atomically using the same pause mechanism. `processHolidayEnd()` resumes all. Holiday management is admin-controlled via `POST /api/admin/holidays`. The cron job at 18:00 daily checks for holidays starting or ending the next day and triggers the appropriate action.

### Admin overrides

`adminOverrideTimer(timerId, action)` supports:

| Action | Effect |
|---|---|
| PAUSE | Pause with current remainingSeconds |
| RESUME | Resume, reset deadline to now + remainingSeconds |
| EXTEND | Add N hours to current deadline |
| RESET | Restart timer from zero for the stage's configured hours |

All admin actions are logged to `AdminTimerOverride` (with `hoursAdded`, `originalDeadline`, `newDeadline`) and `AuditLog` (with `userId = 'SYSTEM'`).

